<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imlut" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imlut</refname><refpurpose>Apply a lookup table to a uint8 image.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imlut(image, lut)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Grayscale or RGB uint8 image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>lut</term><listitem><para>256-entry lookup table.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Mapped image with the same dimensions as <literal>image</literal> and the same datatype as <literal>lut</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = rgb2gray(imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_fruits.jpg")));
lut = uint8(255 - (0:255));
negative = imlut(image, lut);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(negative);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imapplycolormap">imapplycolormap</link></member><member><link linkend="imnormalize">imnormalize</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced with LUT datatype preservation.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
